Senate Resolution 445
By: Senators James of the 28th, Orrock of the 36th and Sims of the 12th
A RESOLUTION
1 Encouraging the Department of Community Affairs to investigate the abusive practices of
2 homeowners' associations, particularly their impact on the elderly and other vulnerable
3 residents in a community; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, homeowners in Georgia are facing increases of abusive practices, retaliatory
5 actions, and financial exploitation by certain homeowners' associations and their boards; and
6 WHEREAS, the unchecked proliferation of short-term rental properties in residential
7 communities has created significant challenges to community stability, homeowner safety,
8 and property values; and
9 WHEREAS, unlicensed property management practices have led to financial
10 mismanagement and abuse of homeowners' rights; and
11 WHEREAS, elderly homeowners are particularly vulnerable to intimidation, harassment, and
12 financial abuse by unscrupulous homeowners' associations; and
13 WHEREAS, individuals taking action against homeowners' associations are subject to
14 retaliatory actions by the association; and
