15 WHEREAS, clear legal protections and enforcement mechanisms are necessary to safeguard
16 homeowners' rights and prevent retaliatory actions against individuals who challenge
17 homeowners' association's conduct.
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that members of this body
19 encourage the Department of Community Affairs to investigate the abusive practices of
20 homeowners' associations, particularly their impact on the elderly and other vulnerable
21 residents in a community to protect those vulnerable individuals and better provide resources
22 and assistance to those individuals where such predatory practices exist.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
24 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Department
25 of Community Affairs.
